    <section class="section">
        <h2>The Problem</h2>
        <p>Every AI you use stores your context as one flat text file. Whatever you said yesterday, your AI doesn't really remember. And to give it context, you have to talk to it&mdash;there's no way to just <em>think</em> and have it become context.</p>
        <p>Meanwhile, your thoughts are scattered across a dozen places. Voice memos here, typed notes there, conversations that start fresh every time. The tools that could help you think better don't actually know you. And the moment you switch AI providers, you start over.</p>
        <p>Parachute is built around a different shape: <strong>an open knowledge layer for humans and AI to think and remember together.</strong></p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <h2>Two pieces, one graph</h2>
        <p>Parachute Daily is how you put thoughts in. Parachute Vault is where they live, and how every AI you use reads them. They share one schema and one storage layer: notes, tags, links. No migration step. No copy-paste. Same data all the way through.</p>

        <div class="products" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
            <div class="product">
                <div style="display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
                    <h3 style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Parachute Daily</h3>
                    <span class="status">Flutter &middot; iOS, Android, macOS</span>
                </div>
                <p>A voice-first journaling and capture app. Three tabs: <strong>Reader</strong> for content to process (briefs, articles, digests), <strong>Capture</strong> for voice memos and typed thoughts, and <strong>Vault</strong> for searching and browsing everything. Local on-device transcription via Sherpa-ONNX, fully offline-capable, with a SQLite cache that flushes to your vault when you reconnect.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Voice-first capture</strong> &mdash; local transcription, works fully offline</li>
                    <li><strong>Three-tab UI</strong> &mdash; Reader, Capture, and Vault for browse and search</li>
                    <li><strong>Phone, web, pendant</strong> &mdash; capture wherever you think</li>
                    <li><strong>Offline-first</strong> &mdash; SQLite cache + pending-write queue</li>
                    <li><strong>Vault sync</strong> &mdash; writes through to your Parachute Vault when connected</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin-top: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0;"><em>The way you put thoughts in.</em> &middot; <a href="https://github.com/ParachuteComputer/parachute-daily" target="_blank">Source &rarr;</a></p>
            </div>

            <div class="product">
                <div style="display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
                    <h3 style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Parachute Vault</h3>
                    <span class="status">Open Source &middot; Self-Hosted</span>
                </div>
                <p>A self-hosted personal knowledge graph, exposed over <a href="https://modelcontextprotocol.io" target="_blank">MCP</a>. Notes, tags, links, full-text search, semantic search, wikilink auto-linking, Obsidian import/export. One command sets up a daemon on port 1940 and registers it with Claude Code. Each vault is its own SQLite database&mdash;run as many as you want.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>20+ MCP tools</strong> &mdash; create, search, tag, link, traverse, find paths, semantic search</li>
                    <li><strong>REST API</strong> &mdash; full CRUD over notes, tags, links, attachments</li>
                    <li><strong>Wikilink auto-linking</strong> &mdash; <code>[[wikilinks]]</code> automatically become graph edges</li>
                    <li><strong>Semantic search</strong> &mdash; vector embeddings via sqlite-vec, OpenAI or local Ollama</li>
                    <li><strong>Obsidian interop</strong> &mdash; import or export existing vaults bidirectionally</li>
                    <li><strong>Multi-vault</strong> &mdash; one daemon, many isolated vaults, per-vault API keys</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin-top: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 0;"><em>Where they live, and how every AI reads them.</em> &middot; <a href="https://github.com/ParachuteComputer/parachute-vault" target="_blank">Source &rarr;</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
