    <section class="section">
        <h2>Built on an open standard</h2>
        <p>The reason Parachute works with every AI you use is <strong>MCP</strong>&mdash;the Model Context Protocol. It's the open standard Anthropic created for connecting AI to tools, and it's now supported by Claude, ChatGPT, and a growing list of others. A Parachute Vault is just an MCP server. You hand any AI a link, and it gets a personal knowledge graph it can read, write, and reason over.</p>
        <p>That's how we stay independent from any single LLM. We're not building the next AI&mdash;we're building the infrastructure underneath. As people settle into different AI camps, Parachute is the layer that travels with them.</p>
